The paper deals with the design and construction of convolutional codes, which are typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and communication complexity (cs.CC) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the properties of these codes in terms of their distance profiles, which is a topic of interest in the sub-categories of data structures (cs.DS) and network information theory (cs.NI). Finally, the paper presents techniques for constructing these codes, which could be relevant to the sub-category of signal processing (cs.SI).
